# Temporary
.codex

# Build-artefact PDFs (regeneratable; exceed the pre-commit
# large-file threshold). Narrow scope to PDF outputs only — the
# `docs/release/pdf/` pipeline source (build.sh, *.typ, README,
# Makefile, etc.) IS tracked so the pipeline is reproducible from
# a fresh checkout.
docs/assets/*.pdf
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock
*.db-shm
*.db-wal

# Reaudit sweep sidecars — ephemeral per-run JSONL state written by
# `elspeth-lints reaudit` for crash recovery. Lives at
# `<allowlist_dir>/.reaudit-state/` (i.e. inside `config/cicd/*/`
# directories that ARE tracked). The sidecars themselves must never be
# committed — they are operator-local run state and contain per-entry
# divergence outcomes that have no audit-trail value outside the
# operator's machine. See `elspeth_lints/core/reaudit_sidecar.py` for
# the full data-model rationale.
**/.reaudit-state/

# atomic_write_text lock files — persistent `.<name>.lock` siblings
# next to managed allowlist YAMLs (the flock idiom; unlinking inside
# the lock races on re-acquire so they stay on disk between runs).
# Operators see them as untracked after the first `justify` /
# `rotate` invocation; they must never be committed. See
# `elspeth_lints/core/atomic_io.py` for the locking rationale.
config/cicd/**/.*.lock

# Release PDF pipeline source is intentionally tracked; generated
# outputs and bulky font source trees are not.
docs/release/*
!docs/release/pdf/output/


